below ground with a radius equivalent to one foot outside of the drip line.
TREE SAVE AREA. An area measured in square feet containing existing healthy tree canopy in a single-family
subdivision or an area containing existing or mitigated off site healthy tree canopy in a commercial development. The
area may include up to five feet beyond the drip line of the tree.
